Number of samples grouped by any categrial variable to illustrate balance of the data set

Samples

  • ITS2 amplicons of N = 77 samples were sequenced

  • FASTQ files were uploaded to DAnIEL web server

  • The cohort was enriched by {{added_projects_count}} projects from the DAnIEL repository of preprocessed projects, namely: {{added_projects}}.

Quality Control

  • Trimmomatic was used to filter high error reads and to trim adapters and primers (Bolger et al., 2014)
  • Samples failed any of these QC criteria were excluded: {{excluded_sample_criteria}}

Denoising

  • DADA2 was used to retrieve amplicon sequence variants (ASV) from quality controlled reads (Callahan et al., 2016)

  • Singletons were not included.

Phylotyping

  • {{ref_database_name}} database was used for phylotyping (Nilsson et al., 2019)

  • Qiime2 Naive Bayes classifier was used for taxonomic classification of denoised sequences (Bolyen et al., 2019)

Normalization and Filtering

  • Hits of denoised sequences were summed up to the genus rank
  • Prevalence filtering: All taxa must be abundant at least 0.01% in at least 5% of all samples.
  • Centered log ratio was the default normalization

Results

Abundance

  • Clustermap of normalized abundances was created using Spearman correlation distance

Normalized feature abundances clustered by Spearman correlation

Alpha diversity

  • 9 distinct features were found

Beta diversity

  • Samples were grouped by cohort
  • Total counts of non chimeric reads were used to calculate all pairwise Bray-Curtis distances between the samples
  • Principal Coordinates Analysis was used for 2D Visualization
  • Grouping by cohort was significant (Adonis PERMANOVA, p <1.0*10-04)

    Ordination Biplot using PCoA and Bray-Curtis metric

Taxon correlation network

  • Pairwise correlations were calculated using SparCC (Friedman and Alm, 2012; Watts et al., 2019)

  • Pseudo p values were calculated using 100 bootstraps which 100 iterations each

  • Correlations were filtered by significance (p < 0.05)
  • P values were adjusted for false discovery rate to yield q values

  • Nodes were colored by order of the taxon

  • Feature selection using ANOVA filtering was performed on 6 models
  • Models were evaluated using nested Cross-validation
